dsDescriptionValue.value:
"Data are provided for 1978 and 1974 on farms, farm characteristics, and farm products for all farms and farms with sales of $2,500 or more. Many categories were expanded for the final file, therefore providing more detailed data than were presented in the preliminary file. Data include farm size, value, land use, and major industrial classification of farms. Additional data cover number of farms and value of specific agricultural products sold; selected farm production expenses including spe cific energy and petroleum products; agricultural chemicals used; number of farms by number of hired farm workers; availability of selected machinery and equipment and market value of all machinery and equipment; type of farm organization and characteristics of the operator such as age, principal occupation, principal place of residence, and number of days work was done off the farm. A detailed inventory of specified livestock and poultry shows the number of each type of animal, the number of farms handling each type, and related value of sales. Data for the major crops produced in each State and county show the number of farms producing each crop, the number of acres involved in production for a specific crop, and the crop yield. Some data fields contain incorrect data. Corrected data have been appended to the end of the tape. A printout showing the correction records begins on page 133 of the documentation."

Data are available for each State and all counties with 10 farms or more
